winlink1000OduAdmLinkName.name: winlink1000OduAdmLinkName
winlink1000OduAdmLinkName.description: Link Name. A change is effective immediately.

winlink1000OduAdmResetCmd.description: Reset Command. A set command with a value of 3 will cause a device reset. HBS only: A set command with a value of 4 will cause a device reset for the entire sector. The read value is always 0.

winlink1000OduAdmAddres.name: winlink1000OduAdmAddres
winlink1000OduAdmAddres.description: ODU IP address. A change is effective after reset. The parameter is kept for backward compatibility. Using the alternative parameter: winlink1000OduAdmIpParamsCnfg is recommended.

winlink1000OduAdmMask.name: winlink1000OduAdmMask
winlink1000OduAdmMask.description: ODU Subnet Mask. A change is effective after reset. The parameter is kept for backward compatibility. Using the alternative parameter: winlink1000OduAdmIpParamsCnfg is recommended.

winlink1000OduAdmGateway.name: winlink1000OduAdmGateway
winlink1000OduAdmGateway.description: ODU default gateway. A change is effective after reset. The parameter is kept for backward compatibility. Using the alternative parameter: winlink1000OduAdmIpParamsCnfg is recommended.

winlink1000OduAdmBroadcast.name: winlink1000OduAdmBroadcast
winlink1000OduAdmBroadcast.description: This parameter is reserved for the Manager application provided with the product.

winlink1000OduAdmHostsTable.name: winlink1000OduAdmHostsTable
winlink1000OduAdmHostsTable.description: Trap destinations table. Each trap destination is defined by an IP address and a UDP port. Up to 10 addresses can be configured.

winlink1000OduAdmHostsIp.name: winlink1000OduAdmHostsIp
winlink1000OduAdmHostsIp.description: Trap destination IP address. A change is effective immediately.

winlink1000OduAdmHostsPort.name: winlink1000OduAdmHostsPort
winlink1000OduAdmHostsPort.description: UDP port of the trap destination. A change is effective immediately.

winlink1000OduAdmHostsSecurityModel.name: winlink1000OduAdmHostsSecurityModel
winlink1000OduAdmHostsSecurityModel.description: Security model used for this trap generation.

winlink1000OduAdmHostsUserName.name: winlink1000OduAdmHostsUserName
winlink1000OduAdmHostsUserName.description: User name used to generate the snmpv3 trap.

winlink1000OduAdmHostsPassword.name: winlink1000OduAdmHostsPassword
winlink1000OduAdmHostsPassword.description: Password used to generate the snmpv3 trap.

winlink1000OduAdmHostsIPv6.name: winlink1000OduAdmHostsIPv6
winlink1000OduAdmHostsIPv6.description: Trap destination IPv6 address. A change is effective immediately.

winlink1000OduBuzzerAdminState.name: winlink1000OduBuzzerAdminState
winlink1000OduBuzzerAdminState.description: This parameter controls the activation of the buzzer while the unit is in install mode. A change is effective immediately. The valid values are: disabled (0), enabledAuto (1), enabledConstantly(2), advancedAuto (3).

winlink1000OduProductId.name: winlink1000OduProductId
winlink1000OduProductId.description: This parameter is reserved for the Manager application provided with the product.

winlink1000OduReadCommunity.description: Read Community String. This parameter always returns ***** when retrieving its value. It is used by the Manager application to change the Read Community String. The SNMP agent accepts only encrypted values.

winlink1000OduReadWriteCommunity.name: winlink1000OduReadWriteCommunity
winlink1000OduReadWriteCommunity.description: Read/Write Community String. This parameter always returns ***** when retrieving its value. It is used by the Manager application to change the Read/Write Community String. The SNMP agent accepts only encrypted values.

winlink1000OduTrapCommunity.name: winlink1000OduTrapCommunity
winlink1000OduTrapCommunity.description: Trap Community String. This parameter is used by the Manager application to change the Trap Community String. The SNMP agent accepts only encrypted values.

winlink1000OduAdmSnmpAgentVersion.description: Major version of the SNMP agent.

winlink1000OduAdmRemoteSiteName.description: Remote site name. Returns the same value as sysLocation parameter of the remote site.

winlink1000OduAdmSnmpAgentMinorVersion.name: winlink1000OduAdmSnmpAgentMinorVersion
winlink1000OduAdmSnmpAgentMinorVersion.description: Minor version of the SNMP agent.

winlink1000OduAdmLinkPassword.name: winlink1000OduAdmLinkPassword
winlink1000OduAdmLinkPassword.description: Link Password. This parameter always returns ***** when retrieving its value. It is used by the Manager application to change the Link Password. The SNMP agent accepts only encrypted values.

winlink1000OduAdmSiteLinkPassword.name: winlink1000OduAdmSiteLinkPassword
winlink1000OduAdmSiteLinkPassword.description: Site Link Password. This parameter always returns ***** when retrieving its value. It is used by the Manager application to change the Link Password of the site. The SNMP agent accepts only encrypted values.

winlink1000OduAdmDefaultPassword.name: winlink1000OduAdmDefaultPassword
winlink1000OduAdmDefaultPassword.description: This parameter indicates if the current Link Password is the default password.

winlink1000OduAdmConnectionType.name: winlink1000OduAdmConnectionType
winlink1000OduAdmConnectionType.description: This parameter indicates if the Manager application is connected to the local ODU or to the remote ODU over the air. A value of 'unknown' indicates community string mismatch.

winlink1000OduAdmBackToFactorySettingsCm.name: winlink1000OduAdmBackToFactorySettingsCmd
winlink1000OduAdmBackToFactorySettingsCm.description: Back to factory settings Command. A change is effective after reset. The read value is always 0.

winlink1000OduAdmWifiRestart.description: A set command with a value of 1 will cause a Wifi restart. The read value is always 0.

winlink1000OduAdmPMPSUSupport.name: winlink1000OduAdmPMPSUSupport
winlink1000OduAdmPMPSUSupport.description: Indicates that PMP SU license is activated

winlink1000OduAdmManagerDownloadURL.name: winlink1000OduAdmManagerDownloadURL
winlink1000OduAdmManagerDownloadURL.description: This is the URL from which management tool can be downloaded

winlink1000OduAdmAntennaDescription.name: winlink1000OduAdmAntennaDescription
winlink1000OduAdmAntennaDescription.description: The is a description of the antenna connected to the ODU

winlink1000OduAdmSwCapabilities.name: winlink1000OduAdmSwCapabilities

winlink1000OduSrvBridging.description: Bridging Mode. Valid values are: disabled (0), enabled (1).

winlink1000OduSrvRingVlanId.description: VLAN ID of the internal ring messages. Valid values are 1 to 4094. Initial value is 0 meaning VLAN unaware.

winlink1000OduEthernetGbeSupported.name: winlink1000OduEthernetGbeSupported
winlink1000OduEthernetGbeSupported.description: Supported Giga bit Ethernet in ODU.

winlink1000OduAirTxPower36.description: Deprecated parameter. Actual behavior is read-only.

A change is effective after link re-synchronization. Valid values: disabled (0), enabled (1). Rewriteable only in Point-To-Point products.
